    "name": "Nicolas Jaar",
    "profile": "Nicolás Jaar (b. 10 January 1990) is an American experimental electronic musician, record producer, composer, DJ, and mixing engineer based in New York. His father is an architect [a=Alfredo Jaar]. He co-founded [url=https://discogs.com/artist/2522005]DARKSIDE[/url] band in 2011 and has been releasing music under various aliases, most notably [url=https://discogs.com/artist/3754267]Against All Logic[/url]. Jaar established two record labels, [url=https://discogs.com/label/245486]Clown & Sunset[/url] (2009–2013) and [l=Other People] (since 2013).\r\n\r\nIn 2008, the same year he enrolled into [l=Brown University], Jaar presented his 12\" debut, [r=1298485], on the Brooklyn-based label [l=Wolf + Lamb Music]. (Nicolas graduated in 2012 with a degree in comparative literature.) Nico Jaar remained active on the NYC underground dance scene, producing multiple \"disco edits\" and \"reworks\" during the [i]nu-disco[/i] resurgence in the early 2010s, with some tracks included on [r=2989464] 12\" and [r=2",
